column3: USD0 is a fiat-backed stablecoin issued by Usual, offering real-time transparency and secured by short-term U.S. Treasury Bills. It aims to bridge traditional finance and decentralized finance, providing stable, reliable, and fully collateralized digital currency for the DeFi ecosystem.
column35: All fees are going in USUAL Treasury
column58: Indirect Method: By depositing USDC into the protocol to receive USD0 on a 1:1 basis. In this method, a third party known as the Collateral Provider (CP) supplies the necessary USYC collateral, enabling users to obtain USD0 without directly holding USYC.
column81: USD0 is 100% backed by the dollar value equivalent to the USYC held by the protocol. USD0 is only issued against the deposit of 1$ of USYC (at the daily value provided by the Hashnote administrator's fund oracle). 100% of USYC is segregated at the previously provided address. The DAO cannot use the funds, they are passively preserved.
column83: USD0 is not collateralized by commercial currency or exposed to a deposit account. Therefore, USD0 is not exposed to the fractional reserve of banks.USD0 is based on the regulated architecture of Hashnote structured in the form of a regulated MMF. Hashnote's assets are in custody at BNY ensuring to avoid any counterparty risk.

column3:
"deUSD (""decentralized US Dollar"") is a fully collateralized synthetic dollar powered by the Elixir Network. Minted by stETH and sDAI, deposited collateral will be used to short ETH, creating a delta neutral position.

Through leveraging this funding rate basis trade on Ethereum, the Elixir network creates a synthetic dollar capturing positive funding rates. Even in a negative funding rate environment however, deUSD is built to be resilient."
column50: ['Stablecoins - sDAI', 'Stablecoins - USDT', 'Cryptocurrencies - stETH', 'Derivatives - Short ETH Perps']
column81: The custodian account are segregated via Off Exchange Settlement solutions that are managed by MPC wallets that have 2/3 signatures such that the custodian, the exchange, and our protocol all don't have individual ability to remove funds.
column83: deUSD is a synthetic dollar asset with the positions created basis trades. Since the backing is not held in traditional banking rails, and entirely on-chain, bankruptcy remoteness does not apply.

column3: USDz is a multichain digital dollar backed by a diversified portfolio of private credit assets. A rigorously underwritten RWA portfolio insulates the protocol from crypto volatility and enables sustainable, consistent ecosystem rewards to promote the adoption of USDz
column11: SPCT collateral is directly held within the mainnet USDz contract.
column58:
"USDz can be directly minted through deposit of SPCT (secured private credit token), by Qualified Minters (QMs). Direct minters must pass KYC/KYB/AML and be whitelisted. QMs can obtain SPCT by depositing USDC or fiat USD.

USDz can also be obtained by depositing USDC to swap for USDz on a 1:1 basis, facilliated by a Qualified Minter which can supply SPCT collateral."
column60:
"Qualified Minters can swap USDz for SPCT on a 1:1 basis, and then SPCT can be redeemed for fiat, USDC, or in-kind securities from the underlying asset portfolio.

Any user may swap USDz on a 1:1 basis for undeployed USDC held by the USDz contract."
column81: USDz is fully backed by the $1 dollar equivalent amount of SPCT which is locked in the USDz contract upon creation of new USDz.
column83: USDz is backed by SPCT (secured private credit token); private credit comprising the backing of SPCT are within bankruptcy remote SPVs, serviced by Percent.

column3: USDL is a yield-bearing ERC-20 stablecoin that distributes the yield generated by reserve assets directly to eligible token holders. USDL is issued by Paxos Issuance MENA Ltd., doing business as Paxos International. Paxos International is prudentially regulated by the Financial Services Regulatory Authority (FSRA) of the Abu Dhabi Global Market (ADGM).
column35: USDL Fee Structure can be found here: liftdollar.com/transparency
column50: ['Corporate Bonds', 'Money Market - Fund', 'Bank Deposits - USD', 'Money Market - RRP']
column58: Minting instructions can be found here: https://docs.liftdollar.com/mint.html
column60: Redeem instructions can be found here: https://docs.liftdollar.com/redeem.html
column81: USDL is backed with cash and cash equivalent assets custodied in legally segregated reserve accounts at financial institutions approved by the regulator.
column83: Lift Dollar is expected to get bankruptcy remote classification from it's regulator in the coming months. Reserve assets are held on third party custodians for the benefit of the token holders and segregated from Paxos International’s corporate balance sheet

column83: The emergency shutdown mechanism has been designed to make sure there is no sequentiality in the process, and that the first-arrived to redeem collateral will not necessarily be the first-served. column81: VEUR/VCHF-token, is accounted as a balance sheet item of VNX Commodities AG itself. In the event of bankruptcy of VNX Commodities AG, it is a legally not defined case, due to the lack of court rulings in Liechtenstein, how the segregation of these assets from the bankruptcy estate will succeed and if as well how parties with contractual claims related to VEUR/VCHF will effectively be awarded.
column83: VEUR/VCHF-token, is accounted as a balance sheet item of VNX Commodities AG itself.
